Martin Kaymer wins PGA title
Martin Kaymer has become the second German golfer to win a major championship.The 25-year-old has emerged last man standing after a dramatic and controversial finish to the PGA Championship in Wisconsin.
Kaymer has won a three-hole play-off against American Bubba Watson after they finished regulation locked at 11-under 277 at Whistling Straits. FULL PGA LEADERBOARD
But American Dustin Johnson was denied a spot in the play-off when he was penalised two strokes for grounding his club in a barely recognisable bunker on the final hole.Australian Steve Elkington was tied for the lead with two holes to play, but finished with two bogeys to come up two shots short of the play-off.